author: @chumblespuzzspuzz4080
text:
People don't talk about how well-done this trailer is.

It's not campy to tug at your heartstrings or overblown and "hyped" like most modern superhero movies. It's a trailer that sums up the film in its entirety without telling you what happens or why. But when you go back and rewatch it knowing what happens in the film, you see everything fall into place. The editing is fantastic, the use of score and sound editing is phenomenal, it's truly one of the greatest film trailers I've ever seen.

author: @thomasle3418
text:
This movie makes morbius' post credit scene much more sense. Sony's long term goal is to create the sinister six. 

Judging by this road map setting up the multiverse and introducing the concept of villians across different dimensions, I think Sony will be doing it differently with an added twist to the multiverse.  I think they are trying to pull off a multiverse Sinister Six battle with a multiverse group of spidermen, as their end game equivalent of MCU's avengers, End Game. 

They are creating their villain verse to, again, recreate this multiversal battle idea between spidermen and its villians across different dimensions, not only through animation wise, but also live action wise. And then, once that's done, they'll merge miles' dimension to the MCU's, as the comics suggest that  miles' dimension collapses and he joins earth 616. Idk if this is replicated in the MCU's earth, as it is a different earth, 19-9999. But, I think there's differently a merge of two different universes soon. That would be hard to do as MCU's timeline remains desperate to the spider-verse and MCU's timeline wants to remain separate to Sony's. Perhaps they will renegotiate in some fashion.

I think the reason Miles and Miguel are fighting is over Uncle Aaron's death.

I think the device that Miguel created is able to go through both dimensions and time and so when Miles says send me back he means back in time to save his uncle. Also the talk of Uncle Ben could refer to how Peter could save Uncle Ben with the device. However Peter states without Uncle Ben they wouldn't become spiderman.

Lastly when Miguel states that he can choose to save 1 life(his uncles) or millions of lives, the millions of lives could link to how Fisk's creation was destroying multiple dimensions and therefore if Miles saves his uncle it could alter the future where they defeat Fisk.

Okay so far I think I have the order of events down:
- Miles gets into an argument with his parents, causing him to be grounded (the scene where he's walking away from them with his hood on)
- His mom talks with him as we see in the first scene
- Gwen travels to his dimension and catches up with him and recruits him (see the first look)
- Miles goes with her and is introduced, but he does something and an alarm is sounded, causing everyone to attack him
- Miles escapes through a multiversal traveling device of some kind, bringing him to Spider-Man India's dimension, but Miguel catches up with him and does the whole chokehold body slam thing (again, see the first look)

author: @Waltham1892
text:
Spiderman and I go way back.
I'm a couple of months older, I was born in May of 1962 and he was first published in August of 1962.  We are both New Yorkers.  We both were brainy kids who didn't fit in.
So, when they swapped out Peter Parker for Miles Morales, I was pissed.
Seemed like another PC get rid of the white guy and swap in a minority move.
Then I saw Into the Spiderverse.
The Animation, the story telling and Miles as a character blew my socks off and reframed Spiderman for me.
Change, when done well, is good.

author: @conspiracypanda1200
text: This movie series has already done so much for Miles Morales as a character. I'm kinda glad that Disney's version almost completely canibalized his general background for their incarnation of Peter Parker. It meant that when this movie came around they had to rework Miles in simple ways that comic book fans had wished he'd been written back when he first appeared. The slightly bigger emphasis on his family dynamics and greater sense of self discovery in becoming Spider-man is a perfect bonus on top of the ingenious animation style, fantastic sound design and fun story.

text:
All spider-man characters (that i noticed or know. and no obvious ones like miles or gwen, and if they are hard to notice i included what they're doing)

1. Spider-man ps4 1:25 (talking to mayday)
2. Mayday Parker 1:25 (talking to ps4 spidey)

3. Bullet proof spidey 1:25 (sitting down)
4. future foundation or synthetic symbiote suit 1:25 (standing still)
5. That one spider-girl with aviator helmet and iron spider legs (she was in LMSH2) 1:26 (drinking coffee)
6. Spider-Woman (MJ) 1:26 (walking with small spider-man)
7. MCU spider-man?? 1:26 (standing with someone else)
8. I dont f'kin know, you decide which is future foundation or not 1:27
9. Bombastic Bag-Man (walking holding some bags) 1:27
10. wolf spider-man (walking) 1:27
11. Mangaverse Spider-man??[its not] (doing naruto run) 1:27-1:28
12. I think the Black Lady is supposed to be Madam Web. 1:37
13. Vulture 1:38
14. Superior or assassin or alex ross spidey. (web-zipping up) 1:56
15. I think thats symbiote spider-man 1:56 
16. idk what that is but its either six armed spider-man with paint on him, or those things from web of shadows 1:57 (attacking miles)
17. Definetely mcu stark suit (swinging at the top) 1:57
18. chunky Armored spider-man MK 1 1:57 (also attacking miles)
19.  Ends of earth suit (again attacking miles) 1:57
20. I think wrestler spider-man or some random homeless 1:58
21.  Classic Iron spider, it may look more white than gold, but its just the filter or shade, since it also turned spider-man ps4's blue to black 1:58
22. Scarlet Spider Kaine (Swinging in front of screen) 1:58 
23. Last Stand Suit 1:59 (swinging in front of screen)
24. Arachnoknight?? 1:59 (chasing miles from the front)
25. Spider-Monkey [not the ultimate guy, an actual spider-monkey] jumping in the background 2:00
26. Spider-Woman (Classic) [Running on the side of that bridge thing) 2:00
27. Scarlet Spider Ben Reilly 2:02 (perching on a metal beam
28. Spider-Man Unlimited (holy shit) 2:02
29. Actually Mangaverse spidey 2:03 (jumping towards miles)

Its kinda impossible to count how many spider ppl are in here, but i tried, the art style and frames make it hard for you to tell if you counted, misscounted, or repeated over a spider person, but just know. Its over 110 spider-men in this so far.

author: @AmanSharma-sn8js
text:
As usual this was freaking awesome beyond words BUT what's important is that this trailer touched a deep human emotion in me & I can almost hear this in my own mom's voice and relate all those words with my daily life struggles.
THIS is what Stan created Spiderman for - to be relatable and inspiring to the common world, to help us see the superhero within us by reflecting it.
This is what superheroes are for, and this is the Marvel we love since decades.
Whoever created this - you have my utmost heartfelt respect. First Wakanda Forever gave me this feeling and now Spider verse is here. I am loving every bit of it, so just THANK YOU!!

- A marvel fan who was feeling he didn't belong here anymore :)

text:
The creative animation techniques was both subtle and mind blowing in the first movie. This movie clearly will surpass the previous in that regard!
Every spider person in the trailer had their own graphic style, dimensions, and even frame rate that payed homage to their origins. Whether it be comic, video game or otherwise.
It was funny seeing the new playstation Spiderman(Earth-1048), possibly walking with his Miles. The Spinneret of Earth-18119  (MaryJane being a spiderwoman as Peter's wife) and many other legit spidermen/women with actual series timelines behind them.
This will be HYPE!!

I definitely saw PS4 Peter, Mayday Parker, Annie May Parker and Mary Jane, The bullet proof suit and something that looks like the weird white suit he had in the comics recently, Maybelle Reiley, Spider-Cop, what I think might be Manga Spidey, Bombastic Bag Man, Werewolf Spidey, Spider-Man Unlimited and a few suits that look like Jessica Drew (Earth 1610) and the Superior Spider-Man.

Also definitely some unique designs. There was one that looked like classic 616 Jessica Drew but with a Scarlet-Spider mask. If only a handful of these get lines I'd burst with excitement.

author: @jjstarrprod
text:
DAMN ! This looks FIRE !
As someone working in the animation industry, I can tell ya : The first one was not only the best Spiderman movie ever, it also completely rocked the animation industry's boat, prior to Arcane ! With these 2 out there showing how it's done in CG animation, even Pixar and Dreamworks are starting to sweat a bit from their butt on their thrones, and had to try new visual styles like Turning Red and Bad Guys (and even Puss in Boots 3 trailer looks like it got some memo from Spiderverse "choppy" 12 frames per second and 2D vfx)

I was so ecstatic about Into the Spiderverse when it came out, I've been watching it 6 times in theaters, each time showing it to different batches of friends (who all fell in love with it !)

I'm SO ready for the second one !
And the 3rd one !

Not only the visuals look even more insane than the first one, but I'm feeling all the actors also gave it their all (so much looking forward to hear Hailee Steinfeld and Oscar Isaac's performances in there after Hawkeye and Moon Knight !)

Antinatalism is the ethical view that negatively values procreation and concludes that procreation is morally wrong under all circumstances. The justifications are: harm/suffering prevention, the questionable nature of gambling with another life, & the impossibility of consent to be born.

In summary:

1. There's no reason to create a child that‚Äôs for the child's sake. For the potential child, birth doesn't solve any problem that it doesn't first create.

2. Existence is imposed without consent. No one chooses to be born or chooses the circumstances of their birth.

3. Everyone experiences at least some suffering, and some people experience disproportionately more suffering than others.

4. Existence brings guaranteed harm for unneeded benefit‚Äîguaranteed harms being: pain, fear, worry, sickness, injury, grief/loss, fatigue, etc.

5. Bringing someone into existence means exposing them to all the harms of this world. It should go without saying that the presence of harm is bad.

6. The only way to guarantee that your kids won‚Äôt ever suffer is by never bringing them into this world in the first place, making the absence of harm good.

7. Even though there is good in this life, the unborn aren‚Äôt deprived of anything since they don‚Äôt exist to miss out on said good, therefore the absence of pleasure is neutral (neither good nor bad).

8. No one has the moral right to inflict serious, preventable harms upon others without their consent.

9. Intentional procreation is intentionally harming your loved ones, a questionable deed.

10. It‚Äôs morally questionable to place someone in a position from which death is the only escape.

11. None of the nonexistent wish to be born but plenty of the living wish they'd never lived;

author: @BDLabs2
text: The Spider-Verse film series is my favorite Spider-Man series so far (even though the sequel hasn't been released yet), because the main protagonist has to develop his character arch while dealing with situations dealing with the multiverse. Once the comics revealed the existence of the multiverse, it never made sense to have super-heroes only deal with localized crimes. Especially with that same crime occurring across an infinite amount of times across the multiverse. I think what would really be a great addition to the Spider-Verse film series is Miles Morales also dealing with curing his villains along with the infinite Spider-Men (Spider-People?). Since the Peter Parkers in _No Way Home_ figured out how to cure villains, it only makes sense for Miles Morales to either learn from them, or figure it out himself to continue doing so. It would also help make his character stand out amongst the other iterations of Spider-Man.

The comparison in growth and change between Miles in this movie and the last is undeniable, but it looks like it's going to be one heck of a story! I love how in the last one, it was more so his father's guidance and dynamic that was being focused on, while here it's his mother's. I think that's a nice shift to see both parental sides of things, and how that plays into Miles and his story. The visuals once again look like they'll be amazing, and I can't wait to see Gwen, Miles, and all other types of Spidermen and how this universe (and others) will be expanded upon!

text: Any chance we could, like, stop exporting our trailers at 16:9 when the film composition is 21:9? It's the epitome of a first world problem and 99% of people definitely don't care, but honestly it just feels like a stupid waste at this point seeing as YouTube has supported 21:9 playback for years *and it takes me all of 2 seconds to resize my sequence in Premiere so I don't see what's so hard about it for you guys.*

Parker as a father and Miguel and Jessica look great too. Not sure what the story is either, assumed it was about the Inheritors from the first teaser with Miguel fighting Miles protecting him while he's trying to save Gwen from an Inheritor but it seems different with everybody trying to fight him. Either way it looks amazing. "And a few other choice adjectives Jameson uses." Hope everybody has a great day.

author: @an-qo6by
text:
I have chills beyond. I think people can be amazing a lot of the time, but the media today has really made an effort to make sure we all think that most of the world is filled with evil and shit people. But then I see this and can imagine all the loads of people that had to find each other, come together, work together, understand the vision, and make something with their heart, sweat, and tears. All just to create something special and share it with the world, to bring some joy and to further this endless array of stories and beautiful art. 

I don't focus enough on the constant stories that are put out, at the end of the day, to help others escape into something and hopefully leave feeling some kind of impact. And there are people who genuinely are just rooting for you and your art, complimenting it, talking about it. It's all what makes me really enjoy and appreciate movies and television. This isn't just art it shows you how people can come together solely to just nerd out over things and I find that wholesome. Oh and of course,

 I really applaud every single person who worked so fucking hard on this. I think we're used to seeing so many well done shows and movies over the years, but still! It amazes me what we have in us. Isn't it crazy? It's not that deep but also I can make it that deep and yeah ahaha

author: @rahul_sanap
text:
2:05  Wait, wait, wait... Something tells me that all 3 of the main spider-men (well, Peter Parker, Miles Morales, and Spider Gwen) are being deceived by Spider-man 2099, and all the spider-men of other universes that have gone a dark path are all gathered there, and then Gwen is like "How is it possible for Spider-men to have gone down a bad path? We are supposed to be the good guys!" and then it's Mile Vs Spider-man 2099, and Peter & Gwen Vs all the other Spider-men.

Pls don't read this if you don't want to, I haven't watched the movie so it isn't a spoiler, but you might be like "OMG! He's right!", but I think how these movies go, someone's gonna die... My first guess is Spider-Gwen (Which I ruled out after a few minutes, because then noone would be there to protect Spider-Gwen's universe, and it would just turn out a bad storyline. So not that.) My second guess is Miles' dad. Miles' identity will get revealed to his mom (Those who have watched Ultimate Spider-man already know this. But I didn't watch the whole episode, and they probably didn't reveal any back story.), and his dad dies climatically, like his uncle.

Thank you Sony Animation, Kemp, Justin, Joaquim, Phil and Chris for all the years of effort you've been doing so far to make the last two films as special as they'll be for us.

text:
Something I notice about this trailer is that it feels like movie moments spliced to be a trailer, rather than purpose made scenes meant to hype up the movie, which will then feel unnatural or obviously trailer moments in the final cut of the movie, which I believe benefits this movies chances of being amazing.  
Not sure if that makes sense, but I hate it when you watch a movie, and suddenly something happens that was so clearly made to be put into a trailer, be it by putting unnecessary comedy in a serious scene, adding a swell of bombastic dialogue for a slight gag in the trailer, or just being chaotic for the sake of making the trailer more exciting and marketable.

text:
looks to me like they're repeating the same storyline from last movie. let me explain my thoughts before jumping.
In the last movie, kingpin wanted to use the Super-Collider to enter the multiverse and find a world where he didn't lose his wife and son. In the trailer we see Spider-Man 2099 (Miguel O'Hara) looking at a video of his daughter. I believed she died and he gonna try and bring her back, same as kingpin. that's why miles, Gwen and peter b. will try to stop him.
later on in the movie it will cause more trouble between the spider-men and they will have to explore the multiverse more, fighting different Spider-Man villains and meeting more spider-men. I believe it will lead eventuality to "Spider-Geddon"- a multiverse war in the 2nd part , "beyond the spider verse". where peter b. and more spider-men will die.

author: @DocumentaryFanboy
text:
I'm gonna be the first to say this but I thought the first movie was extremley overrated. 
It was a mashup of so many diffrent tropes and styles that can work great on their own (superhero comics, manga, noir comics etc.), but make a confusing mess trying to find it's footing for the fans of all of them and failing miserably. 
The humor was weak, forced and bordered on cringe, but I've come to expect that from Marvel movies at this point. 
And finally it tried too hard to blend not only various Spider people, but also cram in as many villains as possible resulting in it being overly staturated. 
Don't get me wrong it's not an objectivley bad movie, it's just poorly structured, weak and tries too hard to be too many things. I still don't get why it won the Oscar for best animated feature film when I can name atleast 5 other far superior animated features that deserved this award more.

author: @oceankim8791
text:
Because I'm an idiot with way too much time on my hands, I made a list of all the alternate Spider-Men I could identify in the trailer (all time-stamps relative to the trailer).

From 1:22 to 1:28 I recognised:
A Spider-Man wearing a version of the ASM Suit (2012) (Yellow Lenses ‚Äì Redesigned Torso) and Assassin Spider-Man of Earth-8351 (Black and Red Suit) talking.

An Alternate Version of PS4 Spidey wearing the Velocity Suit talking with a classic-suit Spider-Man.

The Spider, Peter Parker of Earth 15 ‚Äì In the far back.

PS4 Spider-Man wearing his 1st Game Advanced Suit (As opposed to the redesign for Spider-Man PS4 2) talking to Spider-Girl / Spider-Woman Mayday Parker wearing her original suit.

A Spider-Man wearing the Spider-Armor Mk II and a Spider-Man wearing a variant of the Spider-Armor Mark 1.

Mayday Parker a bit to the left in her second suit alongside 2 other Spider Women I don‚Äôt recognise. 


Spider-Cop alongside Spider-UK and Lady Spider.

Then Mangaverse Spidey in the far back. 

Alongside Mary Jane as Spinneret and Annie Parker from Renew Your Vows in the middle distance.

Then the Bombastic Bag-Man (Minus the f4 Suit) alongside a version of what I assume is Flash Thompson as Spider-Man.



With Werewolf Spider-Man on the far right. 


And Ofc a version of Spider-Woman (based on the logo) at 1:35.

I‚Äôm assuming Jessica Drew, but I could be wrong. 



From 1:55 we see:

Mayday again.

A version of Anya Cortez‚Äôs Spider-Woman / Ara√±a (the female Spider-Man in black)

Spider-Cop

A version of 6-armed Spider-Man (woman?)

The original design for the Spider-Armour MK 1. 

The Spider again.

And then a variant of MCU Peter wearing his Far From Home suit!

Alongside a version of the Black-Cat suit from the PS4 game. 



A version of Kaine Parker‚Äôs rendition of the Scarlet Spider. 


And then from 1:58 onward we have:

2 versions of the Spider.

A version of Future Foundation Spider-Man.

Web-Weaver in the far back (in yellow).

Spider Armour Mk II Spidey again, and also a Spidey wearing the Mk III. 

Flash Thompson Spider-Man again. 

Spider Monkey in the far back.

And a version of MJ‚Äôs Spider-Woman. 


From 2:01, I recognised:

Spider-Man Unlimited Spider-Man

Mangaverse Spidey again.


And, finally, Bombastic Bag-Man once again.

author: @Jack_Woods
text:
It's cool how I can already tell there's really interesting themes of self identity, and doubt, seeing all the different Spiderman attacking each other, and how this would bring into question who considers themselves the good guys and why

Knowing many of the dark turns the Marvel Comics have taken especially with Spiderman, it'll be interesting to see how Miles will deal with the more jaded often tainted Spiderman who do the things they do because they've concluded it's for the better good, while Miles needs to stay true to himself and not let others impose their sense of righteousness onto him, and kill what's left of his innocence

author: @wingspantt
text:
Into the Spider-Verse was so good that, for the first time, I went back and bought comics. I bought the full Spider-Verse collection and read them all, in order. And you know what?

They weren't that good. They had a lot of the fun and world-jumping and wacky characters as these movies... but they didn't have any HEART.

I'm very grateful that Sony and its studios could see the core value of the Spider-verse but write BEYOND it, feel feelings beyond it, and create something where Miles and Peter and Gwen all feel real and vulnerable and, yes, wacky at times, but real. 

Can't wait for this June.

(PS: For anyone who wasn't read the comics, the main plot point is that instead of a scientist creating portals, it's vampires. Vampires that exclusively feed on Spider-Man, from different dimensions. I wish I could say I made that up. But it's dimension-jumping vampires that hop from world to world, eating Spider-Man in all his forms, until the last 30 or so of them band together to defeat the vampires, mainly by tricking them into jumping into a world with no spiders in it. I swear, this is the plot. It's very fun but so, so stupid.)

author: @dspace4514
text:
There is so much to unpack from this one trailer.
-Either Miles seems to miss the others so much he starts to detach from reality somewhat, or he is doing what every Spiderman is doing: detach themselves from their families, thinking that it's better if they are Spider-man more than who they are under the mask.
- The Spiderman must have built a society of some sort after the previous movie. Hopefully we will see Madame Web in this.
- Spiderman 2099 is the villain in this one? As well as the other Spiderman? Could he be trying to change every single origin of the Spiderman, claiming he is helping them?
-No Peni, Noir or Spider-Ham yet. I hope they do appear in the movie, because i love them as well.
-So far, I haven't seen a single symbiote in this. Perhaps they are saving it in case of a third movie?

author: @PhaserFelix
text:
Multiverse is an interesting yet very very boring topic. It makes everything have a reason while also everything useless.
A war won in my multiverse, is lost in another. My best friend killed by a gunshot wound, while in another stabbed. Multiverse is suchs a complicated topic, that it makes some viewers, like myself, kinda feeling like nothing makes sense anymore. Probably because we have yet to have anyone on our earth to understand multiverse or how it would work in a concept to the unwritten rules. If for example, I travel to another multiverse, does that mean there is an multiverse where I did not travel to another one?

Anyway I absolutely loved this movie, but what I wanted to say is that, she is spiderwoman in her multiverse, and he is spiderman in his multiverse. Does this mean that he is basically dating himself?

Both are in fact identified as spiderman/woman in their multiverse, the one and only. If he had not taken up the mask, does it mean she is an result of that, or is she an result of him being born as a women, what I am trying to say.

He is either dating himself, identified as a concept. Or he is dating a multiverse rule break, which basically means he created multiverses where he did not date her. Ima go back to something simpler than this.... Tetris anyone?

author: @elisacastro720
text:
My dear friend, I have an question for you: ‚Äúfor what does it profit a man to gain the whole world and forfeit his soul?" Mark 8:36
It talks about gaining something that is temporary ‚Äì ‚Äúthe whole world‚Äù. But it also a talks about losing something that is eternal ‚Äì¬† your ‚Äúsoul‚Äù. Life is always a trade-off. Why would you lose your own soul? And there is only one answer to this question: your sin. My friend, look into your heart and you will not need any persuasion. Yes, we are sinful. And because of this you are forfeiting your own soul. Your sins makes of you an enemy of God ‚Äì the Judge above all judges, the Judge of all the earth. It‚Äôs an expensive trade-off. And to you I have good news! 
The Bible says, ‚ÄúFor God so loved the world, that he gave his only Son, that whoever believes in him should not perish but have eternal life‚Äù.(John 3: 16) Do you believe it? Terrible thing is to fall into the hands of the living God. And only Jesus, the son of God, through his death on the cross and the resurrection from the dead, can reconcile a sinner with God. He is a mighty Saviour for a great sinner. And Jesus is the one calling you today to repent of your sins and turn to Him. 
"Come to me, all who labour and are heavy laden, and I will give you rest. Take my yoke upon you, and learn from me, for am I gentle and lowly in heart, and you will find rest for your souls. For my yoke is easy, and my burden is light." Matthew 11:28-30
Only Jesus can give us true happiness and peace. He cleans our conscience. And He gives us something not even death(and death takes everything from us) can take away: eternal life.

author: @blinkachu5275
text:
The movie looks amazing but man... that was a very badly edited trailer, from the sound of the mom's voice feeling like it was in a completely different location than Miles's voice, to the abrupt cut from mid emotional music to sudden silence for a few frames and then the modern techno beat.
Whoever cut this together clearly needed a bit more time

Also... please for the love of god... stop with the "THE TRAILER BEGINS NOW" bs. We know. That's why we clicked on the video. We don't need a TRAILER for the TRAILER. The trailer is for the movie and we're here to see the trailer for the movie, not to see the trailer for the trailer in 5 seconds and then see it followed up with the actual trailer. It's such non-sensical use of time management that I don't understand whoever started that trend isn't fired from the industry.
